U.K. Attacks on Libya Supported by 38% of Britons, ICM Poll Says

-- B y   S c o t t   H a m i l t o n
-- 
2011-04-03T08:48:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/u-k-attacks-on-libya-supported-by-38-of-britons-icm-poll-says.html
U.K. and allied military action
against Muammar Qaddafi’s regime in  Libya  is supported by 38
percent of Britons, while 35 oppose it, according to an ICM poll
for  BBC  Radio 4’s Broadcasting House.  The survey found that 65 percent of respondents said
Britain’s involvement “will last for some time,” the BBC
reported on its  website  today. The poll questioned 2,011 Britons
online on March 30 and March 31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Hamilton in London at 
